                    <div class=3D"comment-content comment-content-372375">
                        <div class=3D"moveup">
                        <div class=3D"ttypography"><p>I didn't mean persist=
ent segment tree is better than wavelet tree,and wavelet tree certainly doe=
s better in these kind of problems.I just point out that there exists an al=
ternative way to solve these kind of problems.</p><p>What's more,if we are =
asked to update values and even insert new values,we can use binary search =
tree without rotations(In China it's called Scape-Goat Tree) and segment tr=
ee to solve the problem in O(nlog^2n) time complexity.</p><p>There is a pro=
blem of this kind which you're asked to ask queries of the k-th smallest el=
ement in a range as well as update and insert elements.</p><p><a href=3D"ht=
tp://www.lydsy.com/JudgeOnline/problem.php?id=3D3065">Problem Link(in Chine=
se)</a></p></div>
