                        <div class=3D"ttypography"><p><a href=3D"https://en=
.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/Scapegoat_tree">Scape-Goat Tree on Wikipedia</a></p><=
p>Scape-Goat tree is a kind of binary search tree like Treap and Splay. But=
 it makes itself balanced by reconstruction instead of rotation.Practically=
,if we find the size of the root's left son becomes larger than k*size of t=
he tree or smaller than (1-k)*size of the tree,we just collect all its vert=
ices and rebuild a new binary search tree.Usually k is set to be between 0.=
7 and 0.8.There is a proof why its complexity is O(nlogn) just as Treap and=
 Splay.</p></div>
                        </div>
